elements.description:
`eco-json-schema-input` takes in a JSON schema of type number and string and
contains a `paper-input`, exposing a `value` property that represents the schema.

Validation is handled for strings and number/integers by mapping JSON schema
validation keywords to `paper-input` attributes; form elements will automatically
try and validate themselves as users provide input:

Please see the `eco-json-schema-object` documentation for further information.

properties.name: target
properties.description:
`target` is the target url to upload the files to.
Additionally by adding '<name>' in your url, it will be replaced by
the file name.

properties.name: accept
properties.description:
`accept` is the set of comma separated file extensions or mime types
to filter as accepted.

properties.name: droppable
properties.description: `droppable` indicates whether or not to allow file drop.

properties.name: dropText
properties.description: `dropText` is the  text to display in the file drop area.

properties.name: multi
properties.description: `multi` indicates whether or not to allow multiple files to be uploaded.

properties.name: files
properties.description: `files` is the list of files to be uploaded

properties.name: raised
properties.description: `raised` indicates whether or not the button should be raised

properties.name: noink
properties.description: `noink` indicates that the button should not have an ink effect

properties.name: headers
properties.description: `headers` is a key value map of header names and values

properties.name: retryText
properties.description: `retryText` is the text for the tooltip to retry an upload

properties.name: removeText
properties.description: `removeText` is the text for the tooltip to remove an upload

properties.name: successText
properties.description: `successText` is the text for the tooltip of a successful upload

properties.name: errorText
properties.description: `errorText` is the text to display for a failed upload

properties.name: _shownDropText
properties.description: `_shownDropText` indicates whether or not the drop text should be shown

properties.name: additional
properties.description: `additional` object of key-pair values to send additional values along with file.

properties.name: fileDataName
properties.description: `fileDataName` is the name for the file data in the `formData` object.

properties.name: paperButtonAlt
properties.description: `paperButtonAlt` allows changing the alt property on the paper button

properties.name: paperButtonTitle
properties.description: `paperButtonTitle` allows changing the title property on the paper button
